storyOutputs.text:
In a playground bright and grand,
Where kids would run and skip and stand,
There lived a fisherman so bold,
Whose story needs to be told.

One day while fishing on the slide,
He saw something quite odd outside,
A big red bus came rolling near,
With kids aboard and the driver dear.

The fisherman dropped his fishing line,
And watched the bus with eyes that shine,
He knew right then he had to try,
For a ride on that bus so high.

He ran and hopped onto the bus,
With a fish held tight, causing a fuss,
The driver laughed and gave a cheer,
As they drove around, far and near.

The kids all giggled at the sight,
Of a fisherman on a bus so bright,
They raced and played and had such fun,
Underneath the shining sun.

And as the day came to an end,
The fisherman waved to his new friends,
He thanked the driver with a grin,
For a day of laughter, joy within.

So remember this tale so merry,
Of the fisherman on a bus, so very,
In the playground, where laughter flows,
And silliness, like a river, grows.
storyOutputs.title: The Fisherman and the Red Bus at the Playground
